1. Read all hand-outs

2. Enable internet on your Linux VM

3. Run network commands to familiarize yourself

4. Run tcpdump -i your-linux-interface and view all the traffic coming in.  You can Ctrl C to exit out

5. Update your linux system by running "yum update -y"

6. Install DNS (bind) and go through the configuration file

7. Configure your NTP to synchronize your system with pool.ntp.org

8. Install Apache (httpd) and create your first web page

9. Install and configure sendmail service

10. Install and configure chronyd service.  (Stop NTP if running)
